---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CalculatorCard from '../components/CalculatorCard.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About Us | Battery Calculators"
  description="Learn about Battery Calculators: transparent formulas, open-source calculations, engineering education, and the author behind the platform."
  canonical="https://batterycalculators.com/about"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <Breadcrumb items={[{ label: 'About' }]} />

    <div class="mb-12 border-b border-hairline pb-8">
      <span class="text-label-uppercase text-m-blue-light text-xs block mb-4">PLATFORM BACKGROUND</span>
      <h1 class="text-display-md text-primary mb-6">About Battery Calculators</h1>
      <p class="text-body-md text-body font-light">
        An independent platform offering transparent calculators for battery cell performance, high-power DC distribution lines, and grid-scale energy storage finance.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-12">
      <!-- Section 1: Open Engineering -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Open Engineering</h2>
        <p class="text-body-md text-body font-light mb-4">
          Many tools in the electrical industry are hidden behind subscription walls, bloated dashboards, or proprietary models. We believe that core mathematical formulas should be open, transparent, and easy to run directly in the browser.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body-md text-body font-light">
          Every tool on this website exposes the exact mathematical formulas used to derive its results, along with complete worked examples. This allows you to verify the calculations in your own spreadsheets or scripts.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 2: Why This Site Exists -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Why This Site Exists</h2>
        <CalculatorCard class="bg-surface-soft">
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 text-body-sm text-body">
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-label-uppercase text-primary text-xs mb-2">Transparent Formulas</h4>
              <p class="text-muted">Every calculator shows the exact mathematical formula used. No hidden logic, no black boxes. You can verify every result independently.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-label-uppercase text-primary text-xs mb-2">Engineering Education</h4>
              <p class="text-muted">The Learning Center provides practical guides that explain the engineering principles behind battery sizing, electrical design, and energy storage economics.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-label-uppercase text-primary text-xs mb-2">Practical Battery Sizing</h4>
              <p class="text-muted">Tools designed for real-world scenarios — solar installations, marine vessels, RV systems, home backup, and commercial BESS projects.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-label-uppercase text-primary text-xs mb-2">Open Access Tools</h4>
              <p class="text-muted">All calculators are free to use with no sign-up, no subscription, and no data collection. Everything runs in your browser.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </CalculatorCard>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 3: About the Author -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">About the Author</h2>
        <CalculatorCard class="bg-surface-soft">
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-title-md text-primary mb-1">Dibya Jyoti Sarangi</h3>
              <p class="text-body-sm text-muted">Battery R&amp;D Engineer</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-label-uppercase text-primary text-xs mb-3">Areas of Focus</h4>
              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span class="text-caption text-muted border border-hairline px-2 py-1">Battery Analytics</span>
                <span class="text-caption text-muted border border-hairline px-2 py-1">Marine Battery Systems</span>
                <span class="text-caption text-muted border border-hairline px-2 py-1">Energy Storage Systems</span>
                <span class="text-caption text-muted border border-hairline px-2 py-1">Battery Diagnostics</span>
                <span class="text-caption text-muted border border-hairline px-2 py-1">Engineering Software</span>
                <span class="text-caption text-muted border border-hairline px-2 py-1">Data-Driven Battery Analysis</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-body-sm text-muted mt-2">
              This platform was built to make fundamental battery engineering calculations accessible, transparent, and verifiable for anyone working with energy storage systems.
            </p>
          </div>
        </CalculatorCard>
      </section>

      <!-- Section 4: Technical Specification -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Technical Specification</h2>
        <CalculatorCard class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 bg-surface-soft">
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-label-uppercase text-primary text-xs mb-2">Framework</h4>
            <p class="text-body-sm text-muted">Astro Static Site Generation (SSG) for instant page load times and search indexing.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-label-uppercase text-primary text-xs mb-2">Styling</h4>
            <p class="text-body-sm text-muted">Tailwind CSS v4 compiling lightweight, native CSS custom variables.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="text-label-uppercase text-primary text-xs mb-2">Execution</h4>
            <p class="text-body-sm text-muted">100% client-side TypeScript. No backend logging, data storage, or analytics tracking.</p>
          </div>
        </CalculatorCard>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
